The paper deals with lower bounds for two fundamental graph problems, subgraph isomorphism and graph homomorphism. These problems are closely related to graph theory and algorithms, which are typically studied in the computer science subfields of data structures (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), computational geometry (cs.CG), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and graph theory (cs.GT).
